{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.29",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 29,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 29",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 29 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:1",
      "text": "Job also added, taking up his parable, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:2",
      "text": "Who will grant me, that I might be according to the months past, according to the days in which God kept me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:3",
      "text": "When his lamp shined over my head, and I walked by his light in darkness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:4",
      "text": "As I was in the days of my youth, when God was secretly in my tabernacle?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:5",
      "text": "When the Almighty was with me: and my servants round about me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:6",
      "text": "When I washed my feet with butter, and the rock poured me out rivers of oil?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:7",
      "text": "When I went out to the gate of the city, and in the street they prepared me a chair?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:8",
      "text": "The young men saw me, and hid themselves: and the old men rose up and stood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:9",
      "text": "The princes ceased to speak, and laid the finger on their mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:10",
      "text": "The rulers held their peace, and their tongue cleaved to their throat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:11",
      "text": "The ear that heard me blessed me, and the eye that saw me gave witness to me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:12",
      "text": "Because I had delivered the poor man that cried out; and the fatherless, that had no helper.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:13",
      "text": "The blessing of him that was ready to perish came upon me, and I comforted the heart of the widow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:14",
      "text": "I was clad with justice: and I clothed myself with my judgment, as with a robe and a diadem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:15",
      "text": "I was an eye to the blind, and a foot to the lame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:16",
      "text": "I was the father of the poor: and the cause which I knew not, I searched out most diligently.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:17",
      "text": "I broke the jaws of the wicked man, and out of his teeth I took away the prey.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:18",
      "text": "And I said: I shall die in my nest, and as a palm tree shall multiply my days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:19",
      "text": "My root is opened beside the waters, and dew shall continue in my harvest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:20",
      "text": "My glory shall always be renewed, and my bow in my hand shall be repaired.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:21",
      "text": "They that heard me, waited for my sentence, and being attentive held their peace at my counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:22",
      "text": "To my words they durst add nothing, and my speech dropped upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:23",
      "text": "They waited for me as for rain, and they opened their mouth as for a latter shower.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:24",
      "text": "If at any time I laughed on them, they believed not, and the light of my countenance fell not on earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.29.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:25",
      "text": "If I had a mind to go to them, I sat first, and when I sat as a king, with his army standing about him, yet I was a comforter of them that mourned.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
